            "abstractNote": "Information on the thermal preference of bats goes back to studies carried out since the middle of the 20th century, mainly in North America and Europe. Here we present information on the thermal preference of six bat species in the cloud forests of the Historic Sanctuary of Machu Picchu (Cusco, Peru). The data were obtained in ﬁeld using a thermographic camera and an infrared thermometer. Our results show the intervals and averages of the selected temperatures, as well as the differences between sexes of each species. This information constitutes the ﬁrst effort in Peru to understand the temperature ranges that natural and artiﬁcial bat refuges should have.",
